South Africa Shouldn’t Alter Interest Rate, IMF Says, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-04-12T04:45:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/s-africa-shouldn-t-alter-key-rate-imf-says-bus-day-reports.html
     April 12 (Bloomberg) -- South Africa ’s central bank
shouldn’t alter interest rates, the  International Monetary Fund 
said, Business Day reported.  “We don’t really see from the demand side pressures that
would make you think about changing the stance of monetary
policy now,” Alberto Cuevas, the lender’s senior representative
in South Africa, said, according to the Johannesburg-based
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  